                <h2 class="mt-40">Key challenges for the agriculture industry</h2>
                <div class="gor-100">
                    <div class="h4">
                        <p>Currently, the agriculture industry struggles to reduce food waste, improve traceability
                            throughout its supply chain, and manage rapid payments across organizations, sectors, and
                            jurisdictions. Transportation of foods with short shelf lives, food fraud, and agricultural
                            subsidy management and oversight present additional challenges.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="point-list point-list-accordion">
                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Food waste</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Roughly one-third of all food produced is wasted, with approximately 75% of waste
                                    occurring before it reaches the consumer. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Food traceability</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Consumers want to know where their food comes from, while retailers want to be sure
                                    of what they’re selling. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Food fraud</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Food fraud costs the global agriculture industry $10bn — $15bn annually and affects
                                    up to 10% of all food. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Supply chain tracking</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Organizations struggle to ascertain where each item is in the supply chain, how it
                                    is being treated, and where it comes from. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Payments processing</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    Cross-border payments can involve fees as high as 12% and processing times of seven
                                    days or more, stifling international food trade. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="point point-accordion">
                                <h3>Agricultural subsidy management</h3>
                                <div class="text">
                                    For governments, agricultural subsidy management balances the books; for farmers,
                                    it’s vital. </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
